{
  "stem": "11089.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And men were-- women and children were rescued if their husbands were already in the military.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All the rest were taken away already to Galicia, to-- I know the names all by heart because we received some use from them-- is for three places-- Horodenka, Kolomyia-- Horodenka, Kolomyia, and one more place, where they were thrown right into the Dnieper, into the Dniester.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a river.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Right from the trucks, they were thrown into the rivers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Our people, our villagers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were left only-- out of 60 families, about five were left in the village, til 1944. 1944, they took everybody, including us.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So that was the end of the village.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So the antisemitism increased from day after day, day after day, because the Hungarians, in many, many cases, they were even worse than the Germans.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because they were peasants.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were nothing since the beginning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "All of a sudden, they became rulers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And you know, when a person like this becomes-- becomes a ruler, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Because I've said it many times-- a human being, if he turns into an animal, he's worse than an animal.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because an animal-- you take a lion or a tiger, give him a piece of bread, he will sit down beside you.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But if a human being becomes an animal, he has a method how to kill, how to torture.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You can't stop him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It's even worse.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In my words I once said it, last time, David-- David [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "HaMelech, ?] King David, when he was in trouble, and he said to God, please, dear God, don't let me fall into the hands of a human being if I have to be punished.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "If I have to be punished, you take care of me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "You, God, because you have more passion-- patience.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
